Description: Body sherd of North Ionian pottery rosette bowl; interior: glazed streaky dark-brown with two added red bands; exterior: from top: part of rosette; wide black (fired reddish) band; reserved lower wall; inscription on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 717, no. 751)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.841)
